(57,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:24:50',	'2025-02-28 21:24:50',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dynamic post rendering in WordPress allows you to <strong>automatically display recent content</strong> without manually updating pages.<br><strong>Methods to render posts dynamically:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Query Loop Block:</strong> The built-in way to fetch and display posts in Gutenberg.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Shortcodes:</strong> Use <code>[latest_posts]</code> or custom shortcodes to insert dynamic content.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Theme Templates:</strong> Modify PHP templates in your theme to show posts dynamically.<br>🚀 Try using the Query Loop block and see how posts automatically update when new content is published!</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->',	'How to Dynamically Display Posts in WordPress',	'Learn how to dynamically fetch and display WordPress posts using the Query Loop block and shortcodes.',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'how-to-dynamically-display-posts-in-wordpress',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 22:05:12',	'2025-02-28 22:05:12',	'',	0,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=57',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(58,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:24:50',	'2025-02-28 21:24:50',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dynamic post rendering in WordPress allows you to <strong>automatically display recent content</strong> without manually updating pages.<br><strong>Methods to render posts dynamically:</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Query Loop Block:</strong> The built-in way to fetch and display posts in Gutenberg.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Shortcodes:</strong> Use <code>[latest_posts]</code> or custom shortcodes to insert dynamic content.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Theme Templates:</strong> Modify PHP templates in your theme to show posts dynamically.<br>🚀 Try using the Query Loop block and see how posts automatically update when new content is published!</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->',	'How to Dynamically Display Posts in WordPress',	'Learn how to dynamically fetch and display WordPress posts using the Query Loop block and shortcodes.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'57-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 21:24:50',	'2025-02-28 21:24:50',	'',	57,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=58',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(59,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:25:05',	'2025-02-28 21:25:05',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>WordPress offers two primary content types: <strong>posts and pages</strong>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Posts</strong> are dynamic, appear in chronological order, and are best for blogs or news updates.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Pages</strong> are static and used for content like \"About Us\" or \"Contact.\"<br>When using a <strong>Query Loop block</strong> or a <strong>shortcode</strong>, you can dynamically fetch posts while keeping pages separate.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Understanding WordPress Posts vs. Pages',	'Confused between WordPress posts and pages? Learn the key differences and when to use each.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'54-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 21:25:05',	'2025-02-28 21:25:05',	'',	54,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=59',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(60,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:32:35',	'2025-02-28 21:32:35',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shortcodes in WordPress let you insert dynamic content anywhere on a page or post.<br>Example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code {\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|white\"}}}},\"backgroundColor\":\"black\",\"textColor\":\"white\"} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code has-white-color has-black-background-color has-text-color has-background has-link-color\"><code>\nfunction retro_game_shortcode(){\n    $query = new WP_Query(array(\'post_type\' => \'retroGames\', \'post_per_page\' => 8, \'order\' => \'asc\'));\n    while($query -> have_posts()) : $query -> the_post(); ?>\n    &lt;div class=\"retro-game-container col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-3\">\n        &lt;div>\n            &lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?>\">&lt;?php the_post_thumbnail(); ?>&lt;/a>\n        &lt;/div>\n        &lt;div>\n            &lt;h4>&lt;?php the_title(); ?>&lt;/h4>\n            &lt;?php the_content(); ?>\n            &lt;p>&lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?>\">Learn&lt;/a>&lt;/p>\n        &lt;/div>\n    &lt;/div>\n\n    &lt;?php wp_reset_postdata(); ?>\n    &lt;?php\n    endwhile;\n    wp_reset_postdata();\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, you can use <code>[latest_posts]</code> inside any page or widget to display recent posts!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Using Shortcodes to Display Posts in WordPress',	'Learn how to use shortcodes to display WordPress posts dynamically within pages and widgets.',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'using-shortcodes-to-display-posts-in-wordpress',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 22:04:50',	'2025-02-28 22:04:50',	'',	0,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=60',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(61,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:32:35',	'2025-02-28 21:32:35',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Shortcodes in WordPress let you insert dynamic content anywhere on a page or post.<br>Example:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:code {\"style\":{\"elements\":{\"link\":{\"color\":{\"text\":\"var:preset|color|white\"}}}},\"backgroundColor\":\"black\",\"textColor\":\"white\"} -->\n<pre class=\"wp-block-code has-white-color has-black-background-color has-text-color has-background has-link-color\"><code>\nfunction retro_game_shortcode(){\n    $query = new WP_Query(array(\'post_type\' => \'retroGames\', \'post_per_page\' => 8, \'order\' => \'asc\'));\n    while($query -> have_posts()) : $query -> the_post(); ?>\n    &lt;div class=\"retro-game-container col-sm-12 col-md-6 col-lg-3\">\n        &lt;div>\n            &lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?>\">&lt;?php the_post_thumbnail(); ?>&lt;/a>\n        &lt;/div>\n        &lt;div>\n            &lt;h4>&lt;?php the_title(); ?>&lt;/h4>\n            &lt;?php the_content(); ?>\n            &lt;p>&lt;a href=\"&lt;?php the_permalink(); ?>\">Learn&lt;/a>&lt;/p>\n        &lt;/div>\n    &lt;/div>\n\n    &lt;?php wp_reset_postdata(); ?>\n    &lt;?php\n    endwhile;\n    wp_reset_postdata();\n}</code></pre>\n<!-- /wp:code -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Now, you can use <code>[latest_posts]</code> inside any page or widget to display recent posts!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Using Shortcodes to Display Posts in WordPress',	'Learn how to use shortcodes to display WordPress posts dynamically within pages and widgets.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'60-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 21:32:35',	'2025-02-28 21:32:35',	'',	60,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=61',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(62,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:34:31',	'2025-02-28 21:34:31',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tired of manually updating your WordPress content?</strong> Dynamic blocks can automate this process by fetching and displaying the latest data without editing the page every time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What are dynamic blocks?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>These are <strong>Gutenberg blocks</strong> that fetch and display live data.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Examples: Query Loop block, Latest Posts block, and dynamic text fields.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <strong>How to use them?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Query Loop Block</strong>: Automatically lists recent posts from selected categories.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Latest Posts Block</strong>: Instantly displays the most recent blog posts.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Reusable Blocks</strong>: Update content in one place and see changes everywhere.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <strong>Bonus:</strong> If you want a custom dynamic block, try registering a block using <code>register_block_type()</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dynamic content makes your site more engaging and automated! Try it out today!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Automating Content Updates with Dynamic Blocks in WordPress',	'Learn how dynamic blocks can automatically update your content in WordPress without manual intervention.',	'publish',	'open',	'open',	'',	'automating-content-updates-with-dynamic-blocks-in-wordpress',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 22:04:37',	'2025-02-28 22:04:37',	'',	0,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=62',	0,	'post',	'',	0),
(63,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:34:31',	'2025-02-28 21:34:31',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Tired of manually updating your WordPress content?</strong> Dynamic blocks can automate this process by fetching and displaying the latest data without editing the page every time.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>What are dynamic blocks?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>These are <strong>Gutenberg blocks</strong> that fetch and display live data.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Examples: Query Loop block, Latest Posts block, and dynamic text fields.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <strong>How to use them?</strong></p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Query Loop Block</strong>: Automatically lists recent posts from selected categories.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Latest Posts Block</strong>: Instantly displays the most recent blog posts.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Reusable Blocks</strong>: Update content in one place and see changes everywhere.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ol>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p> <strong>Bonus:</strong> If you want a custom dynamic block, try registering a block using <code>register_block_type()</code>.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Dynamic content makes your site more engaging and automated! Try it out today!</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Automating Content Updates with Dynamic Blocks in WordPress',	'Learn how dynamic blocks can automatically update your content in WordPress without manual intervention.',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'62-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 21:34:31',	'2025-02-28 21:34:31',	'',	62,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=63',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
(65,	1,	'2025-02-28 21:48:05',	'2025-02-28 21:48:05',	'<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>WordPress is a powerful and widely used content management system (CMS) that allows users to create and manage websites with ease. WordPress is highly customizable, offering thousands of themes for design and plugins to extend functionality, making it suitable for blogs, business websites, e-commerce stores, portfolios, and more. It is also SEO-friendly, scalable, and secure, with regular updates to enhance performance and safety.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Whether you are a beginner or an advanced developer, WordPress provides a flexible and user-friendly solution for building websites without needing to code from scratch.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Getting Started with LocalWP</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>To streamline my learning process, I used <strong>LocalWP</strong>, a powerful local development environment for WordPress. LocalWP makes it easy to set up a WordPress site on my computer without needing an online server. It offers features like <strong>one-click installations, database management, and SSL support</strong>, making development faster and more efficient.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Understanding WordPress Editors</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>WordPress offers different ways to create and manage content:</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Block Editor (Gutenberg)</strong> – The default editor that provides a drag-and-drop experience with content blocks. It allows for visually structured content creation.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Classic Editor</strong> – A simple, traditional text-based editor resembling a Word-like interface, perfect for those who prefer a minimal editing experience.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Advanced Custom Fields (ACF)</strong> – A powerful plugin that lets developers create custom fields for posts, pages, and custom post types. This is particularly useful for dynamic and structured content that requires more flexibility than the default editor provides.</li>\n<!-- /wp:list-item --></ul>\n<!-- /wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading -->\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">Understanding Posts and Menus</h2>\n<!-- /wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>I learned how to create and organize <strong>posts</strong> using categories and tags, helping in better content organization. I also explored <strong>WordPress Menus</strong>, which allow for easy navigation customization, enabling users to structure their websites efficiently.</p>\n<!-- /wp:paragraph -->',	'Wordpress',	'',	'inherit',	'closed',	'closed',	'',	'6-revision-v1',	'',	'',	'2025-02-28 21:48:05',	'2025-02-28 21:48:05',	'',	6,	'http://homepage-assignment-1.local/?p=65',	0,	'revision',	'',	0),
